== Per-principal ingress routing: client-cert SAN decides the tenant server ==
   Two probes per identity: a PLAIN HTTPS request (shows the gateway status code) and a gRPC
   request (shows which tenant server Envoy routed to, via x-routed-to + the server's reply).

cert 'tenant_a':  plain-HTTPS status=415   gRPC x-routed-to=spark-connect-tenant-a
            gRPC server reply: Spark Connect request completed without asserting a user_id that matches the verified principal 'tenant_a'
cert 'tenant_b':  plain-HTTPS status=415   gRPC x-routed-to=spark-connect-tenant-b
            gRPC server reply: Spark Connect request completed without asserting a user_id that matches the verified principal 'tenant_b'
cert 'agent_a':  plain-HTTPS status=403   gRPC x-routed-to=DENIED
            gRPC server reply: no tenant route for this principal%0A

no client cert:  plain-HTTPS status=000 (000 => TLS handshake refused: client cert required)
TLS handshake refused (no client cert)

READING: tenant_a/tenant_b certs route to their own server (x-routed-to). An un-granted principal
(agent_a) matches NO route: the plain request returns 403 from the gateway; over gRPC the same deny
surfaces as an HTTP-200 reply carrying x-routed-to=DENIED and grpc-message 'no tenant route'. No cert => TLS refused.
